The United States and Mexico are celebrating 200 years of bilateral relations. They share a commitment to freedom, democracy, and the rule of law. They also have a strong economic and security partnership, making North America the most competitive and dynamic region in the world. This bicentennial is significant as it coincides with the Feast Day of Our Lady of Guadalupe, a holiday with religious and cultural importance for millions of Mexicans and Mexican-Americans. The two countries honor the cultural and familial ties that unite their people and the contributions of Mexican-Americans that have enriched the United States. Throughout history, Mexico and the United States have shown that they are stronger and safer when they stand together. As they enter the next century of their partnership, they emphasize the importance of mutual respect and commitment to shared aspirations.